gomodel:SYNGO_2748  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rationale: NLGN1; neuroligin 1 is a postsynaptic protein. Neurexin-1beta is a presynaptic protein (Fig.4, 6, 7). These proteins are shown to mediate cell-cell adhesion (Fig.2). Together this means that these proteins are involved in 'synapse adhesion between pre- and post-synapse (GO:0099560)'. The relevance of this interaction is shown in the ability of these two protein to be able to induce pre- and postsynaptic differentiation (Fig.6, 7 and ticket #2745).\n\nFig.5: \"Overexpression of neuroligin-1 induces recruitment of neurexin to newly forming synapses\"\nFig.6: \"Induction of neurexin clustering and presynaptic differentiation by purified neuroligin\"\nFig.7: \"Clustering of neurexin is sufficient to induce recruitment of synaptic vesicles\". Experimental description: - Fig.7: \"Hippocampi were removed from embryonic day 18 (E18) rats ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2748" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

